Prague Public Transport will also take a chip for the first time on Wednesday
Wednesday, October 1, 2008, will go down in the history of the Prague Transport Company as the date when the first passengers who will have an electronic coupon in their pockets will board the subway, trams and buses instead of a paper ticket.
At the moment, it can be purchased by about 100,000 people who own an Opencard.
Passengers can buy a 30-day and 90-day and annual coupon (which will apply from 1 January 2009) and at the same time have it uploaded to their chip card at the information centers and workplaces of the Transport Company in the metro stations Muzeum, Můstek, Holešovice Railway Station, Anděl, Roztyly, Letnany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
Coupons can also be purchased via the Internet on the website of the Transport Company www.dpp.cz.
More than 400 customers used the service by the afternoon.
Those who start using the online store can definitely forget about the picking windows in metro stations, where they still had to regularly stand in long queues for paper tickets.
They buy the coupon over the Internet and upload it to their Opencard at one of the thirteen branches of the Municipal Library.
"At these locations, there is a counter with trained service available to help those interested with internet purchases and also upload the purchased coupon to their card," said martin opatrný, a spokesman for the project.
In addition to libraries, it will be possible to record electronic coupons on Opencard also in self-service machines, which are mounted in several metro vestibules.
What do such vending machines look like?
They are red, resemble ticket markers, and passengers may have already noticed them at the metro stations Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"There are now five in the city, but by the end of the year there should be 80," added Opatrný.
Coupon checks the driver's seat of the vending machine
The operation of the vending machines, which will start operating tomorrow, is simple.
Just insert the Opencard smart card into them and the previously paid coupon will upload itself to it.
