The city of New York has thousands of roads, streets, highways and other roads, some famous, others utility only.
But even many veteran taxi drivers and longtime locals have difficulty finding Extra Place, mostly because they've never heard of it.
This tiny alleyway is in the East Village and runs north from First Street - without getting to Second Street - between Bowery and Second Avenue.
