"You're not hugging your white teacher because your white teacher - I mean, there's a cultural barrier," Ms. Nathiri said.
However, civil rights have helped create space for many more Zora Neale Hurstons - black writers, actors and artists who, like her, have risen above prejudice with reckless self-confidence and quotes such as "How can anyone deny themselves the pleasure of my presence!
I won't understand."
