Based on the weighted average price, MUFG will pay 7% less than its book value for Morgan Stanley securities.
And the operation will result in a 20% reduction in earnings per share.
The agreement foresees that MUFG will be able to convert half of its preferential securities into ordinary shares in a year if the latter exchange for a period of time at a price 50% above the exchange price, i.e. about $47.
