The European Equality Summit, hosted this year by France, the current Presiding State of the European Union, began in Paris today.
Lívia Járóková, a Member of the European People's Party for the Fidesz movement, as one of the main speakers of the expert review in her message addressed to the plenary, has turned her attention to segregation in education, as it is one of the most serious injustices affecting Roma children and, moreover, the most serious obstacle to their application.
