The material, invented by a team of researchers, is the development of materials that already exist that use a special carbon structure called carbon dwarf pipes.
Zhong Lin Wang of the Georgia Institute of Technology in Atlanta explains the basis of the glue as a series of pipes laid out like an orderly pile of spaghetti.
Scientists were inspired by the legs of the gecko, covered with microscopic hairs that allow the animal to ensure perfect adcing.
